# docker-compose*.yml build the backend/frontend images with `context: .`
# (the monorepo root, so npm workspaces can resolve correctly), so this is
# the file Docker actually reads — the per-package .dockerignore files
# under packages/*/ document the same excludes for anyone building a
# package standalone with a package-scoped context.
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
**/dist
build
**/build
coverage
**/coverage

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

**/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx

.git
.github
*.md
!README.md

logs
**/logs
uploads
**/uploads
*.log

.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
